    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1969-12-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1969-12-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="173"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d173">
                <head>173. National Security Study Memorandum 85<note n="1" type="source"
                        xml:id="d173fn1">Source: National Archives, Nixon Presidential Materials,
                            <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Files, Box 365, Subject Files,
                            <gloss target="#t_NSSM1">NSSM</gloss>s (43–103.) Secret. A copy was sent
                        to <persName corresp="#p_HRM1">Helms</persName> and <persName
                            corresp="#p_WEG1">Wheeler</persName>.</note>
                    <note n="2" type="summary" xml:id="d173fn2">The President informed the
                        Secretaries of State and Defense, and the Directors of Arms Control and the
                        Office of Science and Technology that, in compliance with <gloss
                            target="#t_NSSM1">NSSM</gloss> 59, he had directed the preparation of a
                        study on all aspects of U.S. policy and programs with respect to toxins. The
                        report was due January 16.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1969-12-31"
                        >December 31, 1969</date>
                </dateline>
                <list type="to">
                    <head>TO:</head>
                    <item>The Secretary of State</item>
                    <item>The Secretary of Defense</item>
                    <item>The Director, Office of Science and Technology</item>
                    <item>The Director, Arms Control and Disarmament Agency</item>
                </list>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT:</head>
                    <item>U.S. Policy on Toxins</item>
                </list>
                <p>As a follow-up to National Security Study Memorandum 59, and in light of the
                    decisions set forth in National Security Decision Memorandum 35, the President
                    has directed a study of all aspects of United States policy and programs with
                    respect to toxins.</p>
                <p>The review should consist of a presentation of current and alternative United
                    States policies and programs with respect to toxins and the pros and cons of
                    each. It should include discussion of research and development programs and
                    objectives, production methods, current capabilities, the military utility of
                    toxins, and the effects upon the United States international position.</p>
                <p>The President has directed the <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss>
                    Interdepartmental Political-Military Group (<gloss target="#t_IPMG1"
                        >IPMG</gloss>) perform this study and that the addressees be included in the
                        <gloss target="#t_IPMG1">IPMG</gloss> for purposes of this study.</p>
                <p>The report of the <gloss target="#t_IPMG1">IPMG</gloss> should be forwarded to
                    the <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Review Group by January 16, 1970.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_KHA1">Henry A. Kissinger</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
